Dear Students,
  
  The department of Computer Science and Engineering is organizing "ENCENDER - A Project Expo" to showcase your completed projects/products on 8th March 2025. This forum is initiated to kindle your pursuit in developing market ready hardware or software products or solutions towards sustainable development goals.
  
  Mark your entry, demonstrate your project and win cash prizes. 
  
  The students are encouraged to submit any completed projects done under the following categories:
  Student Internally Funded Projects
  Task Projects
  Projects done for competition / department
  UG/PG Final Year Projects
  Other projects done under your own interest
  Please register your participation in the link below on or before 26th Feb 2025 
  https://forms.gle/PGWoW1D7p8gtyuLP7
  
  Before registering please ensure to have a ppt that includes the following:
  Problem statement
  Proposed Solution
  Novelty in the proposal
  Deliverables
  Target beneficiaries
  Technology stack
  Screenshots of developed solution (if any)
  Important dates:
  Last date for Project Submission (in PPT) - 26 February 2025 
  Project Selection Intimation - 28 February 2025 
  Payment of Selected Teams (Rs 100 per team of size 3) - March 2, 2025
  Event Date (Presentation and Demonstration) - 8 March 2025
  The brochure is attached for your reference. Feel free to contact us for any queries.
  
  --
  Regards,
  ENCENDER Organizers.

  We?셱e excited to announce From Pixels to Vision Models, an engaging session on image processing and computer vision, hosted by us! With ImageCLEF 2025 now open, this is the perfect time to dive into cutting-edge techniques in computer vision and explore how models interpret images.
  
  Date: 21/02/25 (Friday)
  Time: 1PM - 3PM
  Place: CSE Seminar Hall
  
  What?셲 in Store? 
  1. Image Pre-processing (with a live demo) 
  2. Understanding Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) 
  3. YOLO (You Only Look Once) with a hands-on demo 
  4. Vision Transformers: The Future of Image Recognition 
  5. BLIP (Bootstrapped Language-Image Pre-training) and its applications 
  
  ?렞 Image Captioning Contest !
  Put your learning to the test with our week-long Image Captioning Challenge! Participants will build their own BLIP models using any dataset of their choice. Your models will be evaluated using a benchmark model developed by our team, ensuring a fair comparison.
  
  Looking forward to seeing you at the session and the contest!
  
  Best regards,

IEEE Computer Society Madras Chapter is pleased to announce it's Mega ICT Quiz.
  
  Announcement & CFP: https://lnkd.in/gQG4t2SF
  
  Last date to register: 22nd Feb 2025
  
  About the Quiz: The IEEE Computer Society (CS) Madras Chapter is organizing a Mega ICT Quiz in a leadup to the 80th anniversary celebration of IEEE Computer Society which was founded in 1946. The Quiz will cover the Information and Communication Technology history, concepts, developments trends and current affairs.
  
  Who can participate: Students (College level and School level of 10th grade and above), Researchers, Faculty and Professionals can participate in the Quiz individually. 
  
  Quiz Pattern: The Quiz will be conducted in four stages. Online Prelims, Zonal Orals (in over 10 centres), Semifinal Orals (in two centres), and Final Orals (at Chennai). All Orals will be in-person physical events at various zonal locations in the IEEE Madras Geography.
  
  Certificate of Participation will be presented to all the participants of the online Prelims.
  
  Prizes
  
  Attractive Cash Prizes to all at Zonal, Semifinal & Final Orals.
  
  For toppers & 1st runner-ups (selectively), free ICT related books & subscription to periodicals will be presented. (Currently 12 gifts are available & more likely)
  
  Certificate of Appreciation to all the oral rounds participants. 
  
  The student finalists will additionally get free one year membership in IEEE & IEEE CS. 
  
  Registration Fee: Rs. 50 (fifty only)
  
  Register at https://bit.ly/ieeecs-ict-quiz-registration
  
  Tentative Dates
  
  Last date to Register: 22nd Feb 2025
  Online Prelims: by end of Feb 2025
  Zonal Orals: before end of Mar 2025 
  Semifinal Orals & Final Orals: mid Apr 2025
